lzh_formatted:
  title: 橋西
  author: 鄭樞
  language: lzh
  text: 橋西楊柳盡飛花。信馬尋春到日斜。滿地竹陰門半掩。隔溪亭館是誰家。
korean:
  title: 교서
  author: 정추
  language: kor
  text: |-
    다리 서쪽의 버들은 모두 꽃을 날리는데
    말 가는 대로 봄을 찾다가 해질녘이 되었네
    땅에는 대 그림자 가득하고 문은 반쯤 닫혔는데
    시내 건너 저 정관은 누구 집인고
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_1100&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: West of the Bridge
  author: Jung Chu
  language: eng
  text: |-
    West of the bridge, the willows scatter all their blossoms.
    Following my horse at will, I sought the spring until day's end.
    The ground lies thick with bamboo shadows, the gate half-closed—
    Whose pavilion is that across the stream?
  footnotes:
    - The poem employs a journey motif common in East Asian poetry, where wandering becomes a meditation on transience and solitude.
    - The half-closed gate suggests both invitation and withdrawal, a threshold between the speaker's world and an unknowable other.
